		//only ffcs are flexible-enough to provide randomply placed data values, so we will need to read a 
		//list of screen ffcs, and find one with the values that we want. 
		//While screen scripts have initD, we would not have enough slots for both the shops, and for running an actual screen script. 
		//Although Screen->InitD[] remains an option if desired. 
